{
  "texts": [
    "Subsequently, an in-depth review process was implemented to further identify inadequate items and categorise suitable papers.",
    "Considering the results from the aforementioned databases are quite limited, supplementary relevant papers were added from other less rigorous search engines such as Google Scholar and arXiv.",
    "Notably, although arXiv papers are not normally accepted as trustworthy paper sources, a considerable amount of state-of-the-art works related to LLMs and VLMs have not yet made it to formal publications and can only be found on arXiv, thereby leading to the frequent inclusion of arXiv papers in this review.",
    "Finally, 109 papers have been selected as the basis of this survey, which are further described in Section 3.5.",
    "In recent years, significant advancements have been made in the development of large language models (LLMs) (Zhao et al., 2023a; Chang et al., 2024)."
  ]
}